text: Owosso is the largest city in Shiawassee County in the U.S. state of Michigan. The population was 14,714 at the 2020 census. The city is mostly surrounded by Owosso Township on the east. The city was named after Chief Wosso, an Ojibwe leader of the Shiawassee area. ==References== Category:Cities in Michigan
title: Owosso, Michigan
